{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Raise student loan repayment threshold with inflation, end freeze & cap interest",
        "additional_details": "Threshold freezes mean graduates repay more each year in real terms, even when wages don\u2019t rise much. High interest rates can cause balances to grow faster than repayments, leaving many paying for decades. We believe this is unfair and damages trust in the student finance system.",
        "background": "End the freeze on student loan repayment thresholds, increase them in line with inflation, and cap interest at a rate no higher than the Government\u2019s cost of borrowing.",
